sentences: Jamila Woods (born October 6, 1989) is a Chicago-based American singer, songwriter and poet.
In 2012, Jamila Woods published her first chapbook, entitled The Truth About Dolls.

Her work can be found in the anthologies The Breakbeat Poets: New American Poetry in the Age of Hip-Hop (2015), Courage: Daring Poems for Gutsy Girls (2014), and The UnCommon Core: Contemporary Poems for Learning & Living (2013).
